{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778992040682,"sessionID":"ses_1cbd8e3eeffeyTczgiqNAW5fqm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_KVJifVDmdG4T1UEeRsID0Etk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/src/ontology/Makefile","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/src/ontology/Makefile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: all: stage_release\n2: \n3: SHELL=./stamp.sh\n4: \n5: # ----------------------------------------\n6: # CORE VARIABLES\n7: # ----------------------------------------\n8: \n9: # base URI for all OBO library ontologies\n10: OBO=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo\n11: \n12: # OBO name of this ontology (always lowercase)\n13: ONT=go\n14: \n15: # Base URL for ontology\n16: BASE=$(OBO)/$(ONT)\n17: \n18: # Source file edited by editors\n19: SRC=$(ONT)-edit.obo\n20: \n21: # Staging release directory\n22: RELEASEDIR=../../target\n23: RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS=$(RELEASEDIR)/imports\n24: \n25: # ROBOT is the main release release tool\n26: ROBOT_ENV = ROBOT_JAVA_ARGS=-Xmx12G\n27: ROBOT = $(ROBOT_ENV) robot --catalog catalog-v001.xml\n28: \n29: # OWLTools is a swiss-army knife;\n30: # It does some things robot can't do, but eventually functionality should\n31: # move to robot\n32: OWLTOOLS_ENV = OWLTOOLS_MEMORY=6G\n33: OWLTOOLS = $(OWLTOOLS_ENV) owltools\n34: \n35: #DOSDP is used for turning tsv files into pieces of ontologies for imports\n36: DOSDP_ENV = JAVA_OPTS=-Xmx6G\n37: DOSDP_TOOLS = $(DOSDP_ENV) dosdp-tools\n38: \n39: AMM_ENV = JAVA_OPTS=-Xmx6G\n40: AMM = $(AMM_ENV) amm --silent\n41: \n42: # OWL catalogs map ontology IRIs to local paths\n43: USECAT= --use-catalog\n44: \n45: # obo-centric checks and and filters\n46: PERLCHECK= ../util/check-obo-for-standard-release.pl\n47: PERLFILTER= ../util/filter-obo-for-standard-release.pl\n48: \n49: # Release IRIs are of the form\n50: #  obo/go/releases/YYYY-MM-DD/$FILE\n51: #\n52: # To make snapshot releases:\n53: #\n54: #   $ RELEASE_SUFFIX=SNAPSHOT make prepare_release\n55: #\n56: RELEASEDATE ?= `date +%Y-%m-%d`\n57: RELEASE_SUFFIX=\n58: RELEASE_URIBASE = $(BASE)/releases/$(RELEASEDATE)$(RELEASE_SUFFIX)\n59: \n60: # basic relations are part_of & 3 regulations relations\n61: GO_BASIC_RELATIONS = BFO:0000050 RO:0002211 RO:0002212 RO:0002213\n62: \n63: # extend with has_part, occurs_in and during relations\n64: # - this is the set used in the main go file\n65: GO_MAIN_RELATIONS = $(GO_BASIC_RELATIONS) BFO:0000051 BFO:0000066 RO:0002091 RO:0002092 RO:0002093\n66: \n67: GO_PLUS = extensions/go-plus\n68: GO_GAF = extensions/go-gaf\n69: GO_AMIGO = extensions/go-amigo\n70: GO_LEGO = extensions/go-lego\n71: GO_LEGO_REACTO = extensions/go-lego-reacto\n72: \n73: SPARQLDIR = ../sparql\n74: REPORTDIR = $(RELEASEDIR)/reports\n75: \n76: # ----------------------------------------\n77: # TOP LEVEL TARGETS\n78: # ----------------------------------------\n79: \n80: stage_release: imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl test $(ONT).owl $(ONT).obo $(ONT).json.gz $(GO_PLUS).owl $(GO_PLUS).json.gz go-base.owl $(GO_GAF).owl $(GO_AMIGO).owl $(GO_LEGO).owl $(GO_LEGO_REACTO).owl go-basic.obo go-basic.json.gz extensions/rhea-reactions.ttl imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.obo subset-owls subset-reports generate-mappings\n81: \n82: test: datalog-violations.tsv $(SRC)-check basic-cycles.tsv sparql_test check_all_taxon_constraints_columns change-report.txt reasoned.ofn unsatisfiable present_in_taxon_check.ofn chebi_pH_7_3_check\n83: \n84: travis_test: check_all_taxon_constraints_columns datalog-violations.tsv chebi_pH_7_3_check $(SRC)-check travis_build change-report.txt\n85: \n86: # This target combines features from reasoned.ofn, enhanced.ofn, sparql_test into a faster mode for Travis/GitHub Actions.\n87: # These must be kept in sync.\n88: # The convert step is here only to work around https://github.com/ontodev/robot/issues/1250\n89: travis_build: go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn\n90: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn -o travis_build_dummy_out.ofn verify --queries $(VARGS) -O reports/ merge --collapse-import-closure false -i imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl -i imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl -i ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn -i imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl remove --term 'IAO:0000116' --axioms annotation --signature true query --update ../sparql/add-skos-xrefs.ru --update ../sparql/remove-broad-xrefs.ru --update ../sparql/remove-related-xrefs.ru remove --select 'complement' --drop-axiom-annotations 'oboInOwl:source' reason -r ELK -e asserted-only --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural relax reduce annotate -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$(ONT).owl --annotation owl:versionInfo $(RELEASEDATE) convert --add-prefixes prefixes.jsonld -o travis_build_dummy_out.ofn verify --queries $(SPARQLDIR)/multiple-class-links-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/obsolete-reference-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/missing_superclass-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/different-namespace-violation.sparql -O reports/\n91: \n92: unsatisfiable: $(GO_GAF).owl\n93: \t$(ROBOT) reason --reasoner ELK --input extensions/go-gaf.owl -D $(RELEASEDIR)/core_dump.owl || true\n94: \n95: full_test: test $(ONT).obo\n96: \n97: # note that most derived files are kept separate from source files, in $(RELEASEDIR)\n98: clean: clean_target clean_imports\n99: clean_target:\n100: \trm -rf $(RELEASEDIR)/*\n101: \n102: # copies from staged area to target\n103: prepare_release:\n104: \techo \"Base Version IRI: $(RELEASE_URIBASE)\"\n105: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/extensions &&\\\n106: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/subsets &&\\\n107: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/reports &&\\\n108: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/external2go &&\\\n109: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS) &&\\\n110: \tcp $(ONT).owl $(ONT).obo $(ONT).json $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n111: \tcp imports/*.owl $(RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS) &&\\\n112: \tcp imports/*.obo $(RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS) &&\\\n113: \tcp extensions/* $(RELEASEDIR)/extensions &&\\\n114: \tcp external2go/* $(RELEASEDIR)/external2go &&\\\n115: \tcp go-basic.* $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n116: \tcp go-base.owl $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n117: \tfind subsets/ -maxdepth 1 -type f ! -name '*.tmp' -exec cp {} $(RELEASEDIR)/subsets/ \\; &&\\\n118: \tcp reports/* $(RELEASEDIR)/reports &&\\\n119: \techo \"Release files are now in $(RELEASEDIR)\"\n120: \n121: # deploy to S3\n122: # URLs will be of the form https://s3.amazonaws.com/go-data-product-current/ontology/subsets/go-basic.json.gz\n123: S3CFG = ~/.s3cfg.go-pipeline-push-agent\n124: # https://build.berkeleybop.org/job/release-go-ontology-daily-snapshot/\n125: deploy-snapshot:\n126: \tcd $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n127: \ts3cmd -c $(S3CFG) --acl-public --mime-type=application/rdf+xml sync ./  s3://go-data-product-snapshot/ontology/\n128: \n129: deploy-release:\n130: \tcd $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n131: \ts3cmd -c $(S3CFG) --acl-public --mime-type=application/rdf+xml sync ./  s3://go-data-product-current/ontology/\n132: \ts3cmd -c $(S3CFG) --acl-public --mime-type=application/rdf+xml sync ./  s3://go-data-product-release/$(RELEASEDATE)/ontology/\n133: \n134: \n135: # ----------------------------------------\n136: # GENERIC TRANSFORMS\n137: # ----------------------------------------\n138: \n139: %.gz: %\n140: \tgzip -c $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n141: \n142: %.json: %.ofn\n143: \t$(ROBOT) convert --input $< -f json -o $@\n144: .PRECIOUS: %.json\n145: \n146: # ----------------------------------------\n147: # CHECKS AND BALANCES\n148: # ----------------------------------------\n149: \n150: # TODO: use json form of this file\n151: # See also: https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/13837\n152: # See also: https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18870\n153: GO.xrf_abbs: $(SRC)\n154: \twget http://snapshot.geneontology.org/metadata/db-xrefs.legacy -O $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@ && touch $@\n155: \n156: $(SRC)-check: $(SRC) GO.xrf_abbs\n157: \t$(PERLCHECK) --disable-isa-incomplete --disable-whitespace-check --xref-abbs GO.xrf_abbs $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n158: \n159: # consider using snapshot release\n160: PREVIOUS=go-lastrelease.owl\n161: PREVIOUS_OBO=go-lastrelease.obo\n162: PREVIOUS_PLUS=go-plus-lastrelease.owl\n163: $(PREVIOUS): $(SRC)\n164: \twget $(OBO)/go.owl -O $@ && touch $@\n165: \n166: $(PREVIOUS_OBO): $(SRC)\n167: \twget $(OBO)/go.obo -O $@ && touch $@\n168: \n169: $(PREVIOUS_PLUS): $(SRC)\n170: \twget $(OBO)/go/extensions/go-plus.owl -O $@ && touch $@\n171: \n172: # ensure no IDs are lost\n173: change-report.txt: $(SRC) $(PREVIOUS)\n174: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $(USECAT) $< --verify-changes -p $(PREVIOUS) -o $@ --id-prefix-filter GO: --check-missing-labels && touch $@\n175: \n176: go-owl-diff.md: $(PREVIOUS) go.ofn\n177: \t$(ROBOT) diff --left $(PREVIOUS) --right go.ofn --format markdown -o $@\n178: \n179: go-plus-owl-diff.md: $(PREVIOUS_PLUS) $(GO_PLUS).ofn\n180: \t$(ROBOT) diff --left $(PREVIOUS_PLUS) --right $(GO_PLUS).ofn --format markdown -o $@\n181: \n182: go-obo-txt-diff.md: $(PREVIOUS_OBO) go.obo\n183: \t{ echo \"# Textual diff for go.obo\\\\n\"; echo \"\\`\\`\\`diff\"; diff -u $(PREVIOUS_OBO) go.obo; echo \"\\`\\`\\`\"; } >$@\n184: \n185: go-obo-status.md: $(PREVIOUS_OBO) go.obo ../gh_pages_templates/go-obo-status.md\n186: \t{ echo \"---\"; runoak -i simpleobo:go.obo statistics --group-by-obo-namespace --compare-with simpleobo:$(PREVIOUS_OBO); echo \"---\"; cat ../gh_pages_templates/go-obo-status.md; } >$@\n187: \n188: # ----------------------------------------\n189: # OWL\n190: # ----------------------------------------\n191: \n192: #Uses file provided by Reactome to generate xrefs for import\n193: \n194: ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt:\n195: \twget -O $@ --no-check-certificate https://reactome.org/download/current/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt\n196: \n197: ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt:\n198: \twget -O $@ --no-check-certificate https://reactome.org/download/current/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n199: \n200: imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl: ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n201: \tmkdir -p reactome-tmp\n202: \tsed -i '1s/.*/Identifier\\tName\\tdefined_class/' ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt\n203: \tsed -i '1d' ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n204: \tperl -i.bak -pe 's/[^[:ascii:]]//g' ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt\n205: \tperl -i.bak -pe 's/[^[:ascii:]]//g' ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n206: \tcat ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt >reactome-tmp/combined.txt\n207: \trm ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt.bak\n208: \trm ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt.bak\n209: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --template=xref_dosdp_yaml/reactome_xref.yaml --infile=reactome-tmp/combined.txt --outfile=reactome-tmp/reactome_xrefs.ofn --obo-prefixes=true\n210: \t$(ROBOT) convert --input reactome-tmp/reactome_xrefs.ofn --output imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl annotate --ontology-iri $(BASE)/imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n211: \n212: # Remove reactome_xrefs_import.owl and go_taxon_constraints.owl from imports. These are merged in directly in enhanced.ofn\n213: go-edit-trimmed-imports.obo: $(SRC)\n214: \tgrep -v '^import: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go/imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl' $< |\\\n215: \tgrep -v '^import: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go/imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl' >$@\n216: \n217: go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn: go-edit-trimmed-imports.obo ../util/filter-rhea-xrefs.sc ../resources/rhea.rdf\n218: \t$(AMM) ../util/filter-rhea-xrefs.sc $< catalog-v001.xml ../resources/rhea.rdf $@\n219: \n220: # merge in some imported GO modules\n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 763. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"all: stage_release\n\nSHELL=./stamp.sh\n\n# ----------------------------------------\n# CORE VARIABLES\n# ----------------------------------------\n\n# base URI for all OBO library ontologies\nOBO=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo\n\n# OBO name of this ontology (always lowercase)\nONT=go\n\n# Base URL for ontology\nBASE=$(OBO)/$(ONT)\n\n# Source file edited by editors\nSRC=$(ONT)-edit.obo\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"src/ontology/Makefile","time":{"start":1778992040637,"end":1778992040679}},"id":"prt_e34304ab1001dQJVW1piuAE6ga","sessionID":"ses_1cbd8e3eeffeyTczgiqNAW5fqm","messageID":"msg_e34302e0e0010x6dzeodzxxsYV"}}
