{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778992472756,"sessionID":"ses_1cbd8e3eeffeyTczgiqNAW5fqm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_yd9F3JYxltaYMESwqg9Cg6af","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0018581` because it represents a sub-reaction and is replaced by `GO:0047074`.\n+- Renamed `GO:0047074` to `hydroxyquinol 1,2-dioxygenase activity`, matching the EC accepted name for `EC:1.13.11.37`.\n+- Removed the obsolete term's catalytic-activity participant import axioms so the obsoletion validates cleanly.\n+\n+Validation:\n+- `make travis_build` passed after the edits.\n+\n+Annotation impact:\n+- No direct annotations were found for `GO:0018581`, consistent with the issue discussion.\n*** Add File: PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Summary\n+\n+This change completes the remaining work requested in issue `#25870` by obsoleting `GO:0018581` and moving the accepted EC label onto `GO:0047074`.\n+\n+Changes made\n+\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0018581` (`hydroxyquinol 1,2-dioxygenase activity`):\n+  - changed label to `obsolete hydroxyquinol 1,2-dioxygenase activity`\n+  - preserved the historical definition as an obsolete definition\n+  - added an obsoletion comment explaining that the term is a sub-reaction of `GO:0047074`\n+  - added `replaced_by: GO:0047074`\n+  - removed active-term axioms/xrefs from the stanza, as required for GO obsoletion style\n+\n+- Renamed `GO:0047074` from `4-hydroxycatechol 1,2-dioxygenase activity` to `hydroxyquinol 1,2-dioxygenase activity`:\n+  - retained the existing full-reaction definition based on `RHEA:35595`\n+  - retained the `EC:1.13.11.37 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}` mapping\n+\n+- Updated catalytic-activity participant imports:\n+  - removed the `GO:0018581` participant block from `src/ontology/imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.obo`\n+  - removed the corresponding class block from `src/ontology/imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl`\n+\n+Rationale\n+\n+- The issue discussion concluded that `GO:0018581` captures only a sub-reaction and should be obsoleted in favor of the full `EC:1.13.11.37` reaction term.\n+- `GO:0047074` already carried the exact EC mapping and the complete reaction definition, so it is the appropriate surviving term.\n+- The participant import cleanup was necessary because those imported axioms were reintroducing superclasses for the obsolete term during `travis_build`, causing an `obsolete-reference-violation` failure.\n+\n+Validation and checks\n+\n+- Issue context and comments reviewed from `__issue_context__.json`\n+- Obsoletion workflow checked against local GO obsoletion conventions\n+- Direct annotation check run for `GO:0018581`; no direct annotations were returned\n+- `make travis_build` run after edits and passed\n+\n+Checklist\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: analyzed issue context and identified the requested end state\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: used repository validation workflow to confirm post-change validity; initial run exposed import-level obsolete-term axioms that were then fixed in scope\n+- [ ] RESEARCH: N/A, no new biological assertions or literature references introduced\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: inspected current stanzas and references for `GO:0018581` and `GO:0047074`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: checked relevant GO obsoletion and catalytic-activity precedent; no new logical definitions added\n+- [x] EDITS: used `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` for the edited GO terms\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: removed relationships from the obsolete term; preserved appropriate relationships on the surviving term\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: applied obsoletion and reaction-term considerations relevant to this issue\n+- [x] METADATA: retained tracker items and added correct obsoletion metadata\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: existing RHEA references retained; no new references added\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Su